{"lemma":"سُرَبُ","slug":"سُرَبُ","root":"س.ر.ب","root_slug":"س-ر-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ر-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سُرَبُ","root":"سرب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n19456","","n19458","n19459","n19460","n19461"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8F%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to leak, to seep, to ooze","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to leak, to let through","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of سَرِبَ (sariba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"burrow, den, lair"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"offlet, offtake, air return, flue"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"flock (of birds etc.)"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n19456","headword_ar":"سَرَبَ","root":"srb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suruwbN","text_ar":"سُرُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went forth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he went away."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraba fiY AlA^aroDi","text_ar":"سَرَبَ فِى الاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, A, Mgh, Msb,) aor. as above, (M, Msb,) and so the inf. n., (M, A, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went away"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into the country,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the land"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M, A, Mgh, Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraba fiY HaAjatihi","text_ar":"سَرَبَ فِى حَاجَتِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, M,) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"during the day,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the accomplishment of his want."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa yasorubu Aln~ahaAra kul~ahu fiY","text_ar":"هُوَ يَسْرُبُ النَّهَارَ كُلَّهُ فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawaAy^ijihi","text_ar":"حَوَايِجِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He goes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goes away, all the day, accomplishing his wants"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraba","text_ar":"سَرَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or rather"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraba fiY AlA^aroDi","text_ar":"سَرَبَ فِى الاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went away at random into the country,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the land."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har pp. 448 and 511.) A poet says, (S,) namely, Keys Ibn-El-Khateem, (TA,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"↓ \n      A^an~aY saraboti wakunoti gayora saruwbi"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Whence hast thou gone away at random? for thou wast not one wont to go away at random:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, TA:) thus,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"srbt","text_ar":"سربت"},{"kind":"text","text":", as related by IDrd: accord. to others, ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarayoti","text_ar":"سَرَيْتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarabati AlA_ibilu","text_ar":"سَرَبَتِ الاـِبِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. and inf. n. as above,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The camels went away into the country,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the land, going forth whithersoever they would:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraba","text_ar":"سَرَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said of a stallion [camel]': (Az, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraba","text_ar":"سَرَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) said of a stallion [camel], aor. as above, (S,) and so the inf. n., signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he repaired,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"betook himself, to the place of pasture:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraba AlmaAlu","text_ar":"سَرَبَ المَالُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarobN","text_ar":"سَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the camels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cattle, pastured during the day without a pastor."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraba AlmaA='u","text_ar":"سَرَبَ المَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, Mgh, Msb,) aor. as above, (Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suruwbN","text_ar":"سُرُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mgh, Msb;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sariba","text_ar":"سَرِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarabN","text_ar":"سَرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The water ran"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Mgh) upon the surface of the ground: (A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ansrb","text_ar":"انسرب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) [or the latter signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it ran swiftly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see Har p. 586:)] and in like manner one says of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraAb","text_ar":"سَرَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or mirage],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasorabu","text_ar":"يَسْرَبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarabN","text_ar":"سَرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it runs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHeyth, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saribati AlEayonu","text_ar":"سَرِبَتِ العَيْنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarabN","text_ar":"سَرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarabato","text_ar":"سَرَبَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suruwbN","text_ar":"سُرُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eyn","text_ar":"عين"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"source,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or perhaps (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eye,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masorabN","text_ar":"مَسْرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tsr~bt","text_ar":"تسرّبت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": so says Lh. (M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saribati AlmazaAdapu","text_ar":"سَرِبَتِ المَزَادَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarabN","text_ar":"سَرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mzAdp","text_ar":"مزادة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leathern water-bag"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaraja AlmaA='u sarabFA","text_ar":"خَرَجَ المَا=ءُ سَرَبًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The water came forth from the punctures made in sewing the skin."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [Or]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saribato","text_ar":"سَرِبَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a new [water-skin such as is termed]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qirobap","text_ar":"قِرْبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", or of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mazaAdap","text_ar":"مَزَادَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It had water poured into it in order that the thong"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which it was sewed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"might become moistened, so as to swell, and fill up the holes made in the sewing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b5-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarabN","text_ar":"سَرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below. ―         -b6-  [Golius explains"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraba","text_ar":"سَرَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarabaAnN","text_ar":"سَرَبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as on the authority of the KL, as signifying “"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ingressus fuit in rem, totum subivit implevitve locum:"},{"kind":"text","text":"” but this is a mistake, evidently occasioned by his finding"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarabaAnN","text_ar":"سَرَبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", explained in this sense, instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarayaAn","text_ar":"سَرَيَان"},{"kind":"text","text":", the reading in my copy of the KL.]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarobN","text_ar":"سَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as an inf. n.] is [also]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xarozN","text_ar":"خَرْزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[signifying The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sewing"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a skin or the like]. (Kr, K, TA. [In a copy of the M, I find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~arabu Alxarazu","text_ar":"السَّرَبُ الخَرَزُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"erroneously written for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~arobu Alxarozu","text_ar":"السَّرْبُ الخَرْزُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarabotu Alqirobapa","text_ar":"سَرَبْتُ القِرْبَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarobN","text_ar":"سَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I sewed the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qrbp","text_ar":"قربة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water-skin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"milk-skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TK.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1341},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suriba","text_ar":"سُرِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuniYa","text_ar":"عُنِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [i. e. pass. in form but neuter in signification,] (K,) said of a man, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He became affected with suppression of the feces,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"constipation of the bowels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*ahu HuSorN","text_ar":"اَخَذَهُ حُصْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaSarN","text_ar":"حَصَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to different copies of the K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the entrance of the fume of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"molten"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"silver"},{"kind":"text","text":"[see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usorub~N","text_ar":"اُسْرُبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into the innermost parts of his nose, and other passages,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into his mouth, and the innermost parts of his nose, and his anus,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, * TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and other passages:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) the epithet applied to a man thus affected is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masoruwbN","text_ar":"مَسْرُوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) sometimes he recovers, and sometimes he dies. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","A","Mgh","Msb","S","TA","Az","K"]},{"entry_id":"n19458","headword_ar":"سَرْبٌ","root":"srb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Pasturing"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAl","text_ar":"مَال"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, A, TA,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAl","text_ar":"مَال"},{"kind":"text","text":"[here meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cattle"},{"kind":"text","text":"in general],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that pasture:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAl","text_ar":"مَال"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cattle"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pasturing during the day without a pastor;"},{"kind":"text","text":"an inf. n. used as a subst. in this sense; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAribN","text_ar":"سَارِبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAlN saAribN","text_ar":"مَالٌ سَارِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] signifies the same: (Msb:) or, accord. to IAar, (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA$iyap","text_ar":"مَاشِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other cattle"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (M, K;) thus say IJ and Ibn-Hishám El-Lakhmee: and accord. to Kz, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sirobN","text_ar":"سِرْبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also, [q. v.,] with kesr, signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAlN","text_ar":"مَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA$iyapN","text_ar":"مَاشِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and IO says the like: (TA:) pl. of the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suruwbN","text_ar":"سُرُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, TA,) and some say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoraAbN","text_ar":"اَسْرَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is a pl. of pauc.]. (TA.) Hence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ai*ohabo falaA A^anodahu sarobaka","text_ar":"اِذْهَبْ فَلَا اَنْدَهُ سَرْبَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Go thou away, for I will not drive back thy"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pasturing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb; *) they shall go, (S,) or I will leave them to pasture, (Msb,) where they will; (S, Msb;) meaning, I have no need of thee: (S:) in the Time of Ignorance, they used to divorce by saying thus, (S, M, Msb,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ai*ohabiY falaA A^anodahu sarobaki","text_ar":"اِذْهَبِى فَلَا اَنْدَهُ سَرْبَكِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, M, A.) ―         -b2-  [Freytag also explains it, from the Deewán el-Hudhaleeyeen, as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sheep-fold."},{"kind":"text","text":"]       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"road;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, S, M, A, Mgh, Msb, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sirobN","text_ar":"سِرْبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"with kesr; (M, K;) the latter accord. to Aboo-' Omar and Th, but' disallowed by Mbr, who knew only the former in this sense; said by Ibn-Es-Seed to have been pronounced by AZ with fet-h, and by Aboo-' Omar with kesr: (TA:) and one's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"course;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, * TA;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"way by which one goes."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"surobapN","text_ar":"سُرْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masorabN","text_ar":"مَسْرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xal~i sarobahu","text_ar":"خَلِّ سَرْبَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Leave thou free,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unobstructed, his way"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, Mgh, Msb, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by which he goes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his course;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sirobahu","text_ar":"سِرْبَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr; (M, TA;) accord. to Aboo-' Omar: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xal~i lahu sarobahu","text_ar":"خَلِّ لَهُ سَرْبَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leave thou free,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unobstructed, to him his way."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTolaqa AlA^asiyra waxal~aY sarobahu","text_ar":"اَطْلَقَ الاَسِيرَ وَخَلَّى سَرْبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He loosed the captive and left free to him his way"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) Hence, in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano A^aSobaHa A=minFA fiY sarobihi","text_ar":"مَنْ اَصْبَحَ ا=مِنًا فِى سَرْبِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY mutaqal~abihi","text_ar":"فِى مُتَقَلَّبِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutaSar~afihi","text_ar":"مُتَصَرَّفِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He who has become secure in his scope,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"room, for free action"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or, accord. to one reading, the last words are"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY","text_ar":"فِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sirobihi","text_ar":"سِرْبِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in respect of his wives,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"women under covert,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his household,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"family;"},{"kind":"text","text":"a metaphorical sense, from the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sirob","text_ar":"سِرْب"},{"kind":"text","text":"of gazelles &c. (A, and so in the Fáïk. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sirobN","text_ar":"سِرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) Hence also the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*aA kaAn muxal~aY","text_ar":"اـِذَا كَان مُخَلَّى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~arobi","text_ar":"السَّرْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When he is made to be in ample circumstances; not straitened."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) And you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAsiEu Als~arobi","text_ar":"وَاسِعُ السَّرْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~irobi","text_ar":"السِّرْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Whose way that he pursues is ample."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [But see what follows.])       -A3-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bosom,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"breast;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mind;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadorN","text_ar":"صَدْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mbr, M, K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lawaAsiEu Als~arobi","text_ar":"لَوَاسِعُ السَّرْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is of ample bosom,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mind;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"judgment;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"love:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ample of bosom,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mind; slow of anger."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M. [The latter meaning is assigned in the Msb and TA to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAsiEu Alsirobi","text_ar":"وَاسِعُ السِرْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see the next paragraph.])"}],"source_refs":["M","A","TA","S","Msb","T","Mgh"]},{"entry_id":"n19459","headword_ar":"سِرْبٌ","root":"srb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAribN","text_ar":"سَارِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  [Hence, app.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTiyE","text_ar":"قَطِيع"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamaAEap","text_ar":"جَمَاعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,) [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herd,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of gazelles, (S, M, A, Mgh, Msb, K,) and of oxen, (M, Mgh, Msb,) [app. meaning wild oxen,] and of [wild] asses, (M,) and of wild animals [in general], (S, Msb,) and ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a flock"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herd"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of sheep or goats, (M,) and ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a flock"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of the birds called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTFA","text_ar":"قَطًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) and of birds [in general], (M,) and ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a party,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bevy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of women, (S, M, Msb, K,) &c.; (K;) and, as used by El-' Ajjáj, it is of men also: (Sh, TA:) and a poet of the Jinn, as they assert, used it metaphorically in speaking of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sirob","text_ar":"سِرْب"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the [lizards called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaZaA='","text_ar":"عَظَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) it signifies also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a collection"},{"kind":"text","text":"of palm-trees; (M, K; in some copies of the latter of which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aHol","text_ar":"النَّحْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~axol","text_ar":"النَّخْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"; TA;) so says AHn; and Abu-l-Hasan thinks it to be by way of comparison: and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"surobapN","text_ar":"سُرْبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is like it [in its meanings]: (M: [particularly mentioned in the K as used in the last of the senses above mentioned:]) each of these words is said to be applied to a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qTyE","text_ar":"قطيع"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the birds called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTFA","text_ar":"قَطًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and of gazelles, and of sheep or goats, on the authority of As; and the latter [or each] of them is applied to a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qTyE","text_ar":"قطيع"},{"kind":"text","text":"of women as being likened to gazelles: (TA:) the pl. of the former is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoraAbN","text_ar":"اَسْرَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Sh, M, Msb, TA;) and of ↓ the latter,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"surubN","text_ar":"سُرُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, accord. to the TA,) with two dammehs, (TA,) [in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suruwbN","text_ar":"سُرُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"surobN","text_ar":"سُرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in my MS. copy of the K, [either a contraction of the former pl. or a coll. gen. n. of which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"surobapN","text_ar":"سُرْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the n. un.,]) or both. (TA. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"surobapN","text_ar":"سُرْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below, where the pl. is said to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"surabN","text_ar":"سُرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b3-  [Hence, as some explain them, two phrases mentioned below in this paragraph.] ―         -b4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarobN","text_ar":"سَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence.       -A2-  It is also syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarobN","text_ar":"سَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"road:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a course:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarobN","text_ar":"سَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in two places. ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAlN","text_ar":"بَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlN","text_ar":"حَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"State,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, Msb, K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN waAsiEu Als~irobi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ وَاسِعُ السِّرْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raxiY~u","text_ar":"رَخِىُّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaAli","text_ar":"البَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is in an ample,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unstraitened, state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the meaning may be,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a one is easy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unstraitened, in mind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see what follows, and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAlN","text_ar":"بَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, Msb:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ample of bosom,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mind; slow of anger:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA:) [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAsiEu Als~arobi","text_ar":"وَاسِعُ السَّرْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places near the end of the next preceding paragraph:] MF thinks that for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAl","text_ar":"بَال"},{"kind":"text","text":"we should read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAl","text_ar":"مَال"},{"kind":"text","text":", agreeably with an explanation of a phrase in what here follows. (TA.) ―         -b3-  Also The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalob","text_ar":"قَلْب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heart,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mind"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (M, K:) and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafos","text_ar":"نَفْس"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"self"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (IAar, M, Msb, K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa A=minN fiY sirobihi","text_ar":"هُوَ ا=مِنٌ فِى سِرْبِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is secure in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in respect of, his heart,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"himself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) but IDrd disallows this latter explanation; and says that the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his family,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAl","text_ar":"مَال"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cattle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other property"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his, children;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=mn fY srbh","text_ar":"ا=من فى سربه"},{"kind":"text","text":"were originally used in relation to the pastor, and the stallion [camel], and then extended in its relation to others, metaphorically: (TA:) or the meaning is [simply],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAl","text_ar":"مَال"},{"kind":"text","text":": or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA:) or as expl. above, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarobN","text_ar":"سَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.: or, accord. to Kz,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his way."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) The pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siraAbN","text_ar":"سِرَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (El-Hejeree, M, TA.)       -A3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masorubapN","text_ar":"مَسْرُبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","Mgh","Msb","A","Sh","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n19460","headword_ar":"سَرَب","root":"srb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A subterranean excavation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a habitation"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, TA) of a wild animal, (S, * Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beneath,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ground,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having no passage through it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wakorN","text_ar":"وَكْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) such as has a passage through it is"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1342},{"kind":"text","text":"termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafaqN","text_ar":"نَفَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh, Msb:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"burrow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hole,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,) of a wild animal, (K,) or of a fox, and likewise [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"den"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of a lion, and of a hyena, and of a wolf; and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place into which a wild animal enters:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoraAbN","text_ar":"اَسْرَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, A, Msb.) In the saying in the Kur [xviii. 60],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA@t~axa*a","text_ar":"فَا@تَّخَذَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiylahu fiY A@lobaHori sarabFA","text_ar":"سَبِيلَهُ فِى ا@لْبَحْرِ سَرَبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the fish)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took its way into the sea"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.], Fr says that when the fish was restored to life by the water that came upon it from the fountain [of life], and fell into the sea, its way became congealed, and like a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarab","text_ar":"سَرَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"subterranean excavation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: Zj says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"srbA","text_ar":"سربا"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be considered as put in the accus. case in two ways; either as a second objective complement of the verb, or as an inf. n. [of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sariba","text_ar":"سَرِبَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.]: and AHát thinks that it here means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaAbFA","text_ar":"ذَهَابًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"going away"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or, accord. to IAth,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarabN","text_ar":"سَرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a secret,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hidden, place of passage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as used by El-Moatarid Edh-Dhafaree, it means [simply]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a road,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"way."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) It signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A subterranean channel"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conduit, by which water enters a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAy^iT","text_ar":"حَايِط"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garden,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"walled garden of palm-trees"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TariyqN sarabN","text_ar":"طَرِيقٌ سَرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"road, in which people follow one another continuously."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Flowing water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K: [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saribN","text_ar":"سَرِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water flowing from a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mazaAdap","text_ar":"مَزَادَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leathern water-bag"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water dropping from the punctures made in the sewing"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a water-skin. (A.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Water that is poured into a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qirobap","text_ar":"قِرْبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"skin for water or milk"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when it is new,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mazaAdap","text_ar":"مَزَادَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leathern water-bag"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in order that the thong"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which it is sewed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may become moistened,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so as to swell, and fill up the holes made in the sewing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K","S","Mgh","Msb","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n19461","headword_ar":"سَرِبٌ","root":"srb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Flowing"},{"kind":"text","text":"water. (S, * M. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarabN","text_ar":"سَرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) You say also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mazaAdapN saribapN","text_ar":"مَزَادَةٌ سَرِبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A leathern-water-bag"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}